Today to await/wait for Ctrl+C/sigterm looks something like this:

```C#
var tcs = new TaskCompletionSource<object>();
Console.CancelKeyPress += (sender, e) => tcs.TrySetResult(null);
await tcs.Task;
```

It would be great if there was something more first class:

```C#
public partial static Console
{
    public static Task WaitForCancelKeyPress(CancellationToken cancellationToken = default);
}
```

That would let consumers await the task.

```C#
await Console.WaitForCancelKeyPress();
```

