    Console.CancelKeyPress += (sender, e) =>
    {
        e.Cancel = true;
    };
    ```
- Maybe this would be better as a CancellationToken? But you can't await those either... So maybe if we ever do this https://github.com/dotnet/corefx/issues/23590. You could convert this Task into a `CancellationToken` and use it for cancelling things.

Consider introducing 
```cs
public static bool IsPow2(uint value);
public static bool IsPow2(ulong value);
```
in either `System.Math` or `System.Numerics.BitOperations` (similar to `Log2`). This could be implemented using HW intrinsics ideally or a fast software fallback, e.g
```cs
public static bool IsPow2(uint value)
{
    if (Popcnt.IsSupported)
    {
        return Popcnt.PopCount(value) == 1;
    }

    return SoftwareFallback(value);

    static bool SoftwareFallback(uint value) => (value & (value - 1)) == 0 && value != 0; // Importantly, faster than the PopCount software fallback, hence we don't just call BitOperations.PopCount
}
```

This would consider 0 to not be a power of 2

